<taxonomicName id="4C63C2D3FFCC88210C4A1D3AD5687034" authority="An &amp; Yang, 2009" authorityName="An &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2009" box="[319,576,1626,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevifemura" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9176542FFCC88210C4A1D3AD5687034" box="[319,576,1626,1647]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="403">Platycephala brevifemura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A224D839FFCC88210F3C1D39D5B57034" box="[585,669,1625,1647]" pageId="5" pageNumber="403" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) antenna, lateral view; (D) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (E) epandrium, posterior view; (F) hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DE71BB1D6237753" blockId="6.[146,1103,209,264]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Legs uniformly brown. Hind femur distinctly thickened, about three times longer than wide.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DE71A21D6397702" blockId="6.[146,273,321,345]" box="[146,273,321,345]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B9176542FFCF88220DE71A21D6397702" box="[146,273,321,345]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DE71A09D43A77DA" blockId="6.[146,1103,361,1280]" box="[146,786,361,385]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
Body length 
<quantity id="4C9B14B5FFCF88220C521A09D65177DA" box="[295,377,361,385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="6" pageNumber="404" unit="mm" value="4.9">4.9 mm</quantity>
(male), wing length 
<quantity id="4C9B14B5FFCF88220F1D1A09D59277DA" box="[616,698,361,385]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="404" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
(male).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DC81AEAD7CF755B" blockId="6.[146,1103,361,1280]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
Head (
<figureCitation id="1358A5D5FFCF88220C781AEAD6B777F9" box="[269,415,394,418]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[217,1169,448,1583]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[213,1171,444,1589]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Platycephala brevifemura sp. nov. (male): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) antenna, lateral view; (D) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (E) epandrium, posterior view; (F) hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218408/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Figure 2A–B</figureCitation>
) brown, triangular in profile, about 1.4 times longer than high; frons not strongly produced beyond anterior level of eye, in profile about 0.25 times as long as long axis of eye; gena prominently broadened posterad, anteriorly strongly narrowed below eye; parafacial about 0.05 times as long as long axis of eye. Frontal triangle trapezoid, occupying most area of frons, reaching its anterior margin and semicircular anteriorly; ocellar triangle and surrounding area black; area between eye and frontal triangle depressed and brown-yellow. Setulae and setae on head dark brown. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="1358A5D5FFCF88220CAD1909D56274DA" box="[472,586,617,641]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[217,1169,448,1583]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[213,1171,444,1589]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Platycephala brevifemura sp. nov. (male): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) antenna, lateral view; (D) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (E) epandrium, posterior view; (F) hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218408/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
) brown; pedicel blackish 0.7 times as long as third antennal segment; third antennal segment nearly rectangular, 1.3 times longer than wide, rounded apically, with black dorsal margin; arista pale yellow with brown basal segment, pale short pubescent. Proboscis and palpus pale yellow with pale setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DC81869D4B7727B" blockId="6.[146,1103,361,1280]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
Thorax black, slightly narrower than head; anterior portion of humerus brown, propleuron and upper portion of anepimeron yellow; mesonotum 1.1 times longer than wide, with prominent setigerous punctures; scutellum two times wider than long, with yellow margin. Setulae and setae on thorax pale; katepisternum with some long thin setulae. Legs brown; hind femur (
<figureCitation id="1358A5D5FFCF88220F0318E8D5C275FB" box="[630,746,904,928]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[217,1169,448,1583]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[213,1171,444,1589]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Platycephala brevifemura sp. nov. (male): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) antenna, lateral view; (D) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (E) epandrium, posterior view; (F) hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218408/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Figure 2D</figureCitation>
) short and distinctly thickened, about three times longer than wide and 2.4 times thicker than fore femur; hind tibia somewhat curved. Setulae on legs pale; hind femur with some long setulae. Wing hyaline; veins mostly brown. Relative lengths of costal sections second:third:- fourth54.5:5.8:4. Squama yellow with pale setulae. Halter blackish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DC81F49D52B735B" blockId="6.[146,1103,361,1280]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
Abdomen blackish, light microtrichose; dorsum rugose lightly; venter brown. Setulae and setae black, venter with some pale setulae. Genitalia (
<emphasis id="B9176542FFCF88220EF01F29D4BF723B" box="[901,919,1097,1120]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">„</emphasis>
) (
<figureCitation id="1358A5D5FFCF88220EC51F28D36A723B" box="[944,1090,1096,1120]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[213,280,1625,1647]" captionTargetBox="[217,1169,448,1583]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[213,1171,444,1589]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Platycephala brevifemura sp. nov. (male): (A) head, dorsal view; (B) head, lateral view; (C) antenna, lateral view; (D) hind femur and tibia, anterior view; (E) epandrium, posterior view; (F) hypandrium and phallic complex, ventral view. Scale bar 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5218408" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5218408/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Figure 2E–F</figureCitation>
): epandrium dark brown, longer than wide, with some long setae; surstylus dark brown with many short setulae, its apex narrow, short and directed inward; cercus black with some setulae; hypandrium pale, in dorsal view higher than wide; gonites separated by a distinct suture; pregonites convergent and rounded apically; both distal ends of postgonites acute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DE71E58D630730B" blockId="6.[146,280,1336,1360]" box="[146,280,1336,1360]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B9176542FFCF88220DE71E58D630730B" box="[146,280,1336,1360]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DE71E01D6A97322" blockId="6.[146,385,1377,1401]" box="[146,385,1377,1401]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
<collectingCountry id="F374F9C0FFCF88220DE71E01D7FF7322" box="[146,215,1377,1401]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49A777B2FFCF88220D9D1E01D65D7322" box="[232,373,1377,1401]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DE71ED1D6237392" blockId="6.[146,267,1457,1481]" box="[146,267,1457,1481]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B9176542FFCF88220DE71ED1D6237392" box="[146,267,1457,1481]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DE71EB9D487704A" blockId="6.[146,1103,1497,1553]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
The Latin prefix 
<emphasis id="B9176542FFCF88220C231EBAD6A473A9" box="[342,396,1498,1522]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">brevi</emphasis>
- means short and the Latin 
<emphasis id="B9176542FFCF88220FA11EBAD40A73A9" box="[724,802,1498,1522]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">femura</emphasis>
means femur. The epithet of the species refers to the short and distinctly thickened hind femur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DE71D2AD7DD7039" blockId="6.[146,245,1610,1634]" box="[146,245,1610,1634]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
<emphasis id="B9176542FFCF88220DE71D2AD7DD7039" box="[146,245,1610,1634]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCF88220DE71D12D36770F1" blockId="6.[146,1103,1650,1706]" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">
The new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C63C2D3FFCF88220F521D13D45170D1" authority="Cherian" authorityName="Cherian" authorityYear="1978" box="[551,889,1650,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganta">
<emphasis id="B9176542FFCF88220F521D13D43B70D0" box="[551,787,1651,1675]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">Platycephala giganta</emphasis>
Cherian
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F374F9C0FFCF88220EB01D12D32970D1" box="[965,1025,1650,1674]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="404">India</collectingCountry>
in the lateral shape of head and distinctly thickened hind femur, but can be easily separated
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDCB950FFCE88230DA01BC8D5DC76BA" blockId="7.[213,1169,168,225]" pageId="7" pageNumber="405">
from the latter by the entirely brown hind femur. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C63C2D3FFCE88230E371BC9D49F769A" authorityName="Cherian" authorityYear="1978" box="[834,951,169,193]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Platycephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganta">
<emphasis id="B9176542FFCE88230E371BC9D49F769A" box="[834,951,169,193]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="405">P. giganta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the hind femur is yellow, but partly brown-black (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF2C4A1FFCE88230F3F1BA9D5C176BA" author="Cherian PT" box="[586,745,201,225]" pageId="7" pageNumber="405" pagination="137 - 141" refId="ref4112" refString="Cherian PT. 1978. The genus Platycephala (Diptera: Chloropidae) from India. Orient Insect. 12 (1): 137 - 141." type="journal article" year="1978">Cherian 1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
